<subSubSection id="A1DAC30DE7FE1AFC9611B68C32CE7850" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E2AA376CA5E75AC714B159ABBD919439" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B0ED9E8C235AA7CDD89976B43E47D06" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
As mentioned above, the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="73F99B63CA9FA55B649222CF7B060799" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D0B0C189E8AA62CDED532D6B58038C5E" author="Nee, M" journalOrPublisher="Kurtziana" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="137 - 140" refId="B19" refString="Nee, M, 2000. A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador. Kurtziana 28: 137 - 140" title="A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador." volume="28" year="2000">Nee 2000</bibRefCitation>
) included one specimen here segregated as 
<taxonomicName id="ED40D84A212F174CFD61B122B37484F0" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
. The taxa differ in a suite of characters, detailed above in the discussion of 
<taxonomicName id="05EC202A4711624D336A397898EC584B" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
, but are easy to distinguish by leaf morphology; the leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="06C9CDB100A5BF9AC31C3B6DD7AE978F" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
are coriaceous and shiny above while those of 
<taxonomicName id="36F4ED8EED8F43ADCE7D3DF0BC8F7287" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
are membranous or chartaceous and pubescent above. These stellate trichomes cause the leaves to be asperous to the touch on dry specimens. The stellate trichomes of 
<taxonomicName id="8F21E82A311663E195827079372D186F" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
, while somewhat peltate like those of 
<taxonomicName id="2F616EC4632F0C9BFCFBD0550ECF0EB6" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
, never have the rays fused for more than half their length, and always bear midpoints, even if these are quite tiny. 
<bibRefCitation id="3463134C30C5B0C73E21A89E35A544B7" author="Nee, M" journalOrPublisher="Kurtziana" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="137 - 140" refId="B19" refString="Nee, M, 2000. A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador. Kurtziana 28: 137 - 140" title="A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador." volume="28" year="2000">Nee (2000)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out the morphological similarity between 
<taxonomicName id="409BEBA1C1FD4F35A8610C02BB2ED09A" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
and the similarly widespread 
<taxonomicName id="69FD67E15373A3C13F29E2CB5905CEE3" authorityName="Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Dun" authorityYear="1816" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lepidotum">Solanum lepidotum</taxonomicName>
Dunal and 
<taxonomicName id="E146F2EA4DC4DB56A5D34AC7175BD360" authorityName="Walp" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schlechtendalianum">Solanum schlechtendalianum</taxonomicName>
Walp. The latter two taxa have more lateral inflorescences that are not borne on erect peduncles. 
<taxonomicName id="93FE0B4D8CCB2B273C01520310D6B774" authorityName="Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Dun" authorityYear="1816" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lepidotum">Solanum lepidotum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3EAE423876709CBB84F0887FEFA856FA" authorityName="Walp" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schlechtendalianum">Solanum schlechtendalianum</taxonomicName>
show a similar pattern of hair diversity to 
<taxonomicName id="E0EBF52CF6F539A2F4A480485804FA37" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="493FA686771382F405F1169B165DC095" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
; each species pair has one member with porrect-stellate trichomes with the rays not fused (
<taxonomicName id="7B10901B6655C9E80CBD4C0492005D23" authorityName="Walp" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schlechtendalianum">Solanum schlechtendalianum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="04FC6A810291902E9008849EB6F6DB19" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
) and one with peltate trichomes (
<taxonomicName id="FA5E6ABF9B5F8FD2178C44DD4453EDC8" authorityName="Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Dun" authorityYear="1816" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lepidotum">Solanum lepidotum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="26F4277EAEED6BD34107E2902E4384C9" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
). Taxonomists working with primarily morphological data have traditionally recognised different sub-groupings for taxa with stellate and peltate trichomes (
<bibRefCitation id="3FC56DF6E39C53BFA18A2D008D8FFA51" author="Seithe, A" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="261 - 336" refId="B27" refString="Seithe, A, 1962. Die Haararten der Gattung Solanum L. und ihre taxonomische Verwertung. Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 81: 261 - 336" title="Die Haararten der Gattung Solanum L. und ihre taxonomische Verwertung." volume="81" year="1962">Seithe 1962</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="48CD0E2E103B15F36F48C260686636ED" author="Carvalho, Ld'AF" journalOrPublisher="Pesquisas, Botanica" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="5 - 83" refId="B4" refString="Carvalho, Ld'AF, 1996. Especies de Solanum das secoes Cernuum Carv. &amp; Sheph. e Lepidotum (Dun.) Seithe v. Hoff. (Solanaceae). Pesquisas, Botanica 46: 5 - 83" title="Especies de Solanum das secoes Cernuum Carv. &amp; Sheph. e Lepidotum (Dun.) Seithe v. Hoff. (Solanaceae)." volume="46" year="1996">Carvalho 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="23174D493ACD355130D7A3E37A9F9320" author="Nee, M" editor="Nee, M" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="285 - 333" refId="B18" refString="Nee, M, 1999. Synopsis of Solanum in the New World. In: Nee, M, Symon, DE, Lester, RN, Jessop, JR, Eds., Solanaceae IV: Advances in Biology and Utilization. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew: 285 - 333" title="Synopsis of Solanum in the New World" volumeTitle="Solanaceae IV: Advances in Biology and Utilization." year="1999">Nee 1999</bibRefCitation>
), but molecular data (
<bibRefCitation id="3B3CFC01B4369890B6D79D4005C11497" author="Bohs, L" journalOrPublisher="A festschrift for William G. D'Arcy: The legacy of a taxonomist. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="27 - 49" refId="B3" refString="Bohs, L, 2005. Major clades in Solanum based on ndh F sequence data. A festschrift for William G. D'Arcy: The legacy of a taxonomist. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 104: 27 - 49" title="Major clades in Solanum based on ndh F sequence data" volume="104" year="2005">Bohs 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9C6F26823D33527C75653F739B87E1F6" author="Weese, TL" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="445 - 463" refId="B32" refString="Weese, TL, Bohs, L, 2007. A three gene phylogeny of the genus Solanum (Solanaceae). Systematic Botany 32: 445 - 463" title="A three gene phylogeny of the genus Solanum (Solanaceae)." volume="32" year="2007">Weese and Bohs 2007</bibRefCitation>
) suggest a more complex situation.
</paragraph>
